sentences: Frances Ethel Scarborough (10 January 1880 â€“ 9 December 1956) was an English pianist, composer and politician.
She was born in Crouch End, London and died in Graffham, Sussex.
Scarborough was also active in the Conservative Party, for which she stood in Ebbw Vale at the 1935 United Kingdom general election, taking second place with 22.2% of the vote.
